get website running
communicate from website to server using websockets
get phone app
communicate from app to server using websockets
get biometrics from phone app(sign up)
in server, use those to create a user
sign in user based on biometrics(sign in)

--stretch--
use bluetooth to determine proximity and allow sign in without username

-- mega stretch --
allow sign in from any device with the app(guest mode type thing)


------------
OPERATIONS
------------

enable wsgi(gunicorn) for performance and proxying.
see https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-serve-flask-applications-with-uswgi-and-nginx-on-ubuntu-18-04
and @jamiro look at athena also
